<title>NORWAY: Storebrand backs Aker /RGI merger.</title>
<headline>Storebrand backs Aker /RGI merger.</headline>
<dateline>OSLO 1996-11-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Norwegian insurance company Storebrand ASA supports the proposed merger between offshore engineer and construction group Aker ASA and investment group RGI ASA, the Oslo Bourse said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>It said Storebrand had served notice it would vote for the merger at an Aker extraordinary shareholders' meeting on Thursday.</p>
<p>Storebrand controls about three percent of Aker stock.</p>
<p>The merger is widely expected to go through, creating one of the largest industrial groups in Scandinavia with annual revenues of 19 billion crowns and a market capitalisation of nine billion crowns. The proposed deal values one Aker share at 2.15 RGI shares.</p>
<p>--Oslo newsroom +47 22 42 50 41</p>
